ActCanada Elections Act
SubjectOrder Designating the Minister of Public Safety and Emergency Preparedness as the Minister for the Purposes of the Canada Elections Act
PrecisOrder (1) repealing Order in Council P.C. 2021-941 of October 26, 2021; and (2) designating the Minister of PUBLIC SAFETY AND EMERGENCY PREPAREDNESS, a member of the King’s Privy Council for Canada, as the Minister for the purposes of the CANADA ELECTIONS ACT.
